<item>
            <title>[KAFKA-2721] Avoid handling duplicate LeaderAndISR requests</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-2721</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Upon controller migration, the new controller will try to resend all the LeaderAndISR requests for any on-going partition reassignments. This can then lead to duplicate such requests sent to the same broker.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Upon receiving such requests, today brokers do not detect if, for example, it is already the leader for the requested becoming-leader-partition, and does the logic such as 1) stop fetching 2) coordinator migration, etc which is not necessary.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
